Gilde Raises 170 Million Euros of Loans to Back RP Group Buyout

-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 
2011-06-30T09:55:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/gilde-raises-170-million-euros-of-loans-to-back-rp-group-buyout.html
Gilde Buy Out Partners BV raised 170
million euros ($247 million) of leveraged loans for its buyout
of RP Group BV, which operates holiday parks in the Netherlands
and  Germany , according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Gilde, which manages more than 2 billion euros, said on May
19 it agreed to buy a majority stake in Kamperland, Netherlands-
based RP Group, which posted 233 million euros of sales in 2010
and operates 31 holiday parks, Gildeâ€™s  website  shows.  ABN Amro Bank NV, Rabobank International, Deutsche Bank AG
and Friesland Bank NV arranged the financing which includes 62.5
million euros of seven-year loans paying an initial interest of
425 basis points more than the euro interbank offered rate,
Bloomberg data show. A basis point is 0.01 percentage point.  Details of the financing are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
